        Puts or takes an item.
        Specified by:
        transfer in class SynchronousQueue.Transferer<E>
        Parameters:
        e - if non-null, the item to be handed to a consumer; if null, requests that transfer return an item offered by producer.
        timed - if this operation should timeout
        nanos - the timeout, in nanoseconds
        Returns:
        if non-null, the item provided or received; if null, the operation failed due to timeout or interrupt -- the caller can distinguish which of these occurred by checking Thread.interrupted.
